# Track 8 — Claude Code Operational Rules

> Location: ~/Dropbox/ALOMA/claude-code/track-8/
> Last updated: 2026-03-09
> Scope: LOCAL Node.js job search agent system ONLY

---

## ⛔ CRITICAL — This is NOT ALOMA

Track 8 is a local Node.js application. It has NO relation to:
- AKS / Kubernetes
- Flux GitOps
- CockroachDB
- NATS
- Azure infrastructure
- Alertmanager / Prometheus

Do NOT apply ALOMA operational rules here. Do NOT run kubectl commands. Do NOT check Flux.

---

## System Overview

| Agent | Port | Directory | Purpose |
|-------|------|-----------|---------|
| Signal Scanner | 3033 | signal-scanner/ | Monitors LinkedIn/news for job signals |
| Agent 2 — Research Hub | 3035 | agent2-research/ | Company research via web search |
| Agent 3 — Scorer | 3038 | agent3-scorer/ | Scores companies (ELNS+H or exec search firm) |
| Agent 4 — Contact Research | 3036 | agent4-contact-research/ | Finds right contact, FullEnrich enrichment |
| Agent 5 — Outreach Drafter | 3037 | agent5-outreach-drafter/ | Drafts emails, saves to Gmail Drafts (never sends) |
| Agent 6 — Email Scan | 3034 | agent6-email-scan/ | Scans Gmail for inbound replies, classifies, writes to Attio |
| Dashboard | 3030 | dashboard/ | Health dashboard + workspace iframe view |

---

## Execution Rules

### 1. Local only
All agents run locally on Mac. No Docker. No cloud deployment. No port-forwarding.
Start command: `node server.js` from the agent directory.
Logs: `/tmp/track8-<agent-name>.log`

### 2. Health endpoint
Every agent exposes `/api/health` returning `{"status":"ok"}`.
The dashboard polls this. claude-auto polls this. Never change the path.

### 3. Models
- Default: `claude-sonnet-4-6`
- Classification only: `claude-haiku-4-5-20251001`
- NEVER use `claude-opus-4-6` in automation

### 4. MCP transport — stdio only
Gmail, Attio MCPs use `StdioClientTransport`. NOT HTTP.
Env vars: `GMAIL_MCP_COMMAND`, `GMAIL_MCP_ARGS`, `ATTIO_MCP_COMMAND`, `ATTIO_MCP_ARGS`
MCP clients are singletons — reset to null on failure, call `closeClient()` on SIGTERM/SIGINT.

### 5. Gmail — Drafts only, never send
Agent 5 saves to Gmail Drafts. It never calls send. No exceptions.

### 6. Attio — Agent 6 only
Only Agent 6 writes to Attio. Agent 4 never writes to Attio.

### 7. FullEnrich — manual only
No MCP, no automation. Agent 4 enriches via FullEnrich REST API.
Key location: `agent4-contact-research/.env` — `FULLENRICH_API_KEY=`

### 8. arago always first
In any outreach draft, arago proof point is always listed first. Non-negotiable.
No em-dashes in any draft output.

### 9. POSITIONING.md is live config
`agent5-outreach-drafter/POSITIONING.md` — read on every draft. Edit via Agent 5 Positioning tab or directly.
Never hardcode positioning content in source code.

### 10. SQLite is the persistence layer
Each agent has its own SQLite DB in `data/`. No shared DB. No external DB.
DB files: `data/agent<N>.db` or `data/<name>.db` — check `db.js` for actual filename.

