## Known Pitfalls

- MCP stdio only — HTTP transport silently fails
- Use `$HOME` not `~` in bash commands from Claude Code
- No bash brace expansion in Claude Code — use explicit mkdir with full paths
- `/tmp` is ephemeral — all persistent output to Dropbox paths
- Health endpoint is `/api/health` not `/health` — mismatch breaks claude-auto detection
- Agent 5 draft approved → saved to Gmail Drafts, then notifies Agent 4 (graceful fail if Agent 4 down)
- FullEnrich requires real API key — mock mode returns placeholder data without it
- CLAUDECODE env var blocks nested Claude Code sessions — unset when spawning subprocesses

---

## Instruction File Format

Max 100 lines, numbered STEPs, one bash block per step with inline verification.
Header on every file:
```
# Execute from: ~/Dropbox/ALOMA/claude-code/track-8/
# Before executing, read: ~/Dropbox/ALOMA/claude-code/track-8/CLAUDE.md
```

End every file with a SUMMARY step (10-15 lines max: STEP pass/fail, key findings, errors verbatim).
Move completed instructions to `../instructions/completed/` after execution.

